data.output: Keisha loved many things, but her 2 favourite things in the world were the smell of petrol and sunny days. Keisha also did not mind the smell of diesel but often found if she went to the petrol station to help pump her husbands car the diesel pump would often get stuck which was one of Keisha's irritants. On this particular sunny Saturday morning Keisha set out to the nearest park to her meet her friends to have a picnic, she decided to walk but really wished she drove so the smell of petrol would be breezing through her hair.

On Friday morning, just before work, Harry went downstairs from his room to see he had received a letter. On the letter was a 1st class stamp and Harry's first and last name in big, bold letters which automatically let Harry know this letter was urgent. Harry quickly opened the letter and saw it was a letter from his great Aunt letter letting him know he should remember to send the mini fridge she sent him as it was the only fridge she had.

Daisy also wanted to be a  transplant surgeon. The thought of holding an organ in her hand and having to comply with the regulations of the GMC board everyday excited her. However, due to the financial demands of medical school, Daisy had to open a lash business, which seemed to be taking up more time then she has ever proposed. During her last year Daisy decided to close her well known business empire down and focus on studying to become the surgeon she always wanted to be.

If there was one thing about Dawn she hated missing direct debit payments, but due to the doom and gloom of the cost of living crisis Dawn had missed a lot. This made Dawn feel sad but it did not let her forget about the fact that she got to exist everyday in a world where there was always a way to make money, such as using the website Prolific.
